<HEADLINE>
EFFORTS BLOTTED OUT BY ERRORS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC had just finished its triple overtime thriller
with Oregon, and around midnight Saturday coach Paul Hackett
finally emerged from the locker room.
</P>
<P>
   He might have commented on the drama of Oregon's 33-30 victory
at Autzen Stadium. Or the courageous effort of quarterback Mike Van
Raaphorst filling in for the injured Carson Palmer.
</P>
<P>
   But Hackett couldn't hide his bitter disappointment over the
errors USC committed, with a school-record 21 penalties, the most
in a Pacific-10 Conference game.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're not a very good football team right now,'' Hackett said.
``We're back to square one. We are nowhere right now. We
self-destructed at every turn. We lost every opportunity under the
sun. It's disappointing.
</P>
<P>
   ``Mistakes were everywhere. When you have mistakes and
penalties, it just dulls some wonderful efforts by the receiver
corps and defensive line. We wasted a hell of an effort by Mike Van
Raaphorst.''
</P>
<P>
   Hackett's frustration centered on some critical moments that
probably cost USC the game.
</P>
<P>
   __ USC was called for unsportsmanlike conduct after scoring the
go-ahead touchdown to take a 23-20 lead with 3:08 remaining.
Offensive lineman Faasea Mailo took off his helmet _ a violation of
NCAA rules _ and drew the penalty.
</P>
<P>
   That meant a routine extra point suddenly was kicked 15 yards
farther back, and a bad snap sailed through holder John Fox's
hands.
</P>
<P>
   Mailo, who was a Mormon missionary for two years, was not even
aware he broke a rule by removing his helmet.
</P>
<P>
   ``I guess I've been away from the game too long,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   __ The Trojans seemed to have the game sealed after the botched
extra point, when Troy Polamalu forced a fumble on the ensuing
kickoff, and Aaron Graham recovered to give USC the ball at the
Oregon 22 with 2:59 left.
</P>
<P>
   Chad Morton then scored on a sweep play, but the touchdown was
called back on a holding penalty.
</P>
<P>
   ``The holding penalty on the touchdown was a shame,'' Hackett
said.
</P>
<P>
   __ Note: Hackett said Sunday he will cut the time of players who
have been committing penalties, by rotating in some reserves this
week. He didn't identify which positions are affected. Fullback
Charlie Landrigan will start in place of Brennan Ochs this week. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
REPORT CARD &QL; 
__ GAME: 3 &QL; 
__ RESULT: Oregon 33, USC 30 &QL; 
__ RECORD: 2-1, 0-1 &QL; 
__ THIS WEEK'S GPA: 2.38 &QL; 
__ CUMULATIVE GPA: 2.84 &QL; 
__ NEXT GAME: Oregon State &QL; 
QUARTERBACKS &QL; 
Mike Van Raaphorst deserved a purple heart in relief. Will Carson
Palmer even want his redshirt year? What's Jason Thomas' phone
number? &QL; 
B+ &QL; 
RUNNING BACKS &QL; 
Does anyone else think Chad Morton has lost a step? Sultan
McCullough is apparently being saved for track season. &QL; 
D+ &QL; 
RECEIVERS &QL; 
R. Jay Soward was reintroduced to the offense and it paid off
nicely. Steve Stevenson showed promise with his two receptions
before being hurt. &QL; 
A &QL; 
OFFENSIVE LINE &QL; 
The good: Pass protection of Van Raaphorst was impressive. The bad:
Nonexistent run blocking and six false starts. &QL; 
C &QL; 
DEFENSIVE LINE &QL; 
The unsung heroes of the team. Ryan Nielsen has an NFL future and
is USC's most improved player. Ennis Davis had his best game of the
season. &QL; 
A- &QL; 
LINEBACKERS &QL; 
Markus Steele had 16 tackles and Zeke Moreno 13 in two courageous
efforts. The strongside position seems to be the weak link. &QL; 
B+ &QL; 
DEFENSIVE BACKS &QL; 
They did a nice job holding down Oregon's receivers _ by the
jersey, the arm or any other means you could think of. &QL; 
D+ &QL; 
SPECIAL TEAMS &QL; 
Yikes! Three missed field goals are one thing, but when did
snapping the ball become so difficult? &QL; 
D &QL; 
COACHING &QL; 
It was a memorable game, but someone has to take the blame for 21
penalties. That's 47 in three games, for those keeping score at
home. &QL; 
C- &QL;
</P>
