<SLUG> BC-FBC-PALMER-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SEASON OVER FOR PALMER?
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC quarterback Carson Palmer suffered a broken
collarbone in Saturday night's 33-30 loss to Oregon and probably
will be lost for the remainder of the regular season.
</P>
<P>
   Palmer is officially listed as being out 6-8 weeks, which would
place his return around late November, when the Trojans only have
games with UCLA and Louisiana Tech on the schedule.
</P>
<P>
   The sophomore said Sunday that he would do everything in his
power to return in time for the UCLA game.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't want to sit out. I want to play,'' Palmer said. ``I
want to play in the UCLA game. It's going to be tough to come back
this year, but I'm going to try.''
</P>
<P>
   Palmer believed he might heal even faster, citing a broken
collarbone he suffered in his sophomore year at Santa Margarita
High that sidelined him for just four games. But that injury was
only a crack in the collarbone, while this latest incident was a
clean break and considered more serious.
</P>
<P>
   An intriguing sidelight is that Palmer could redshirt under NCAA
rules, because he did not play in more than three games this
season.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't want to sit out,'' Palmer said. ``I want to play.
(But) if the coaches think it's best to redshirt, then I'll
redshirt.''
</P>
<P>
   As for speculation the issue is moot anyway, because he might
turn pro early, Palmer said, ``I plan on being here for four years.
Maybe five now.''
</P>
<P>
   Asked if Palmer would return for the UCLA game, USC coach Paul
Hackett said, ``I wouldn't rule that out, but I would say that's
unlikely.''
</P>
<P>
   Hackett said it was too early to decide if Palmer would
redshirt.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's a distinct possibility,'' he said. ``I don't feel I can
make that decision when I (don't know how fast he will heal).''
</P>
<P>
   Palmer regretted that he tried to gain a few extra yards before
being hit by Oregon rover Michael Fletcher just two plays before
halftime.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was stupid, I don't know why I did it,'' Palmer said. ``It
would have been more macho to go out of bounds.''
</P>
<P>
   It was a rough weekend for the Palmer family. Carson's little
brother, Jordan, received a concussion Thursday playing quarterback
for the Santa Margarita junior varsity team.
</P>
<P>
   With Palmer out, junior Mike Van Raaphorst takes over as USC's
starter, with senior John Fox the backup. Fox started nine games in
1997. He will now move to quarterback full-time after playing
linebacker this year.
</P>
<P>
   If USC needs a No. 3 quarterback, it would be sophomore walk-on
Matt Dalton.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm nervous,'' Hackett said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
