<P>
   JAPAN-COMPUTERSCREENS (Mobara, Japan) _ In the center of this
verdant peninsula, just east of Tokyo, is one of the world's
largest computer screen factories, where hundreds of humming robots
and uniformed workers in clean rooms assemble 200,000 flat panels a
month. But they still cannot work fast enough to feed the enormous
appetite for the flat-panel screens. By Calvin Sims.
