<HEADLINE>
DID U.S. WIN ONE FOR THE QUIPPER?
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Before the champagne dries on Ben Crenshaw's matted-down fringe
of hair, something oughta be considered before the Ryder Cup
competition rides across the pond to someplace called The Belfry in
2001:
</P>
<P>
   Replace cryin' captain C'shaw with TV golf evangelist Johnny
Miller.
</P>
<P>
   'Cause if it weren't for Miller's straight-shootin' comments on
the NBC telecast during Saturday afternoon's dreadful U.S.
exhibition, Crenshaw wouldn't have had any material to use to help
fire up his dirty dozen on Saturday night after the stupid
four-ball competition was over and good ol' American one-on-one
play started.
</P>
<P>
   ``(Justin) Leonard doesn't have anything going for him. . . . My
hunch is Leonard needs to go home and watch it on TV,'' Miller
assessed when he heard Gentle Ben was going with a hunch and
passing up Jeff Maggert (who asked to sit, by the way) for
Saturday's late matches to go with a guy who missed a few critical
morning putts.
</P>
<P>
   Leonard responded Sunday with his flat stick along with some
unflattering response directed at Miller: ``I'm not going home.''
</P>
<P>
   Mission accomplished.
</P>
<P>
   Miller tried to take the reverse criticism with some humor, and
he was much more subdued on the air late Sunday after watching the
remarkable comeback. Maybe because the victory meant something to
him, too, even though the network told its guys not to be homers on
the telecast.
</P>
<P>
   Maybe Crenshaw can stay as captain. Just as long as NBC
televises the event in two years _ and brings along Miller.
</P>
<P>
   __ NBC's Jim Gray gushed in front of Crenshaw, his wife and
daughter: ``We can see you all have tears in your eyes right now.''
The daughter said loud enough for the mike to pick it up: ``I
don't.'' Gray didn't have a follow-up for her. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Rumor was that the Americans were so desperate after the
first two days that an INS agent was hired to try to encourage
defections. Except for Monty. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ How much does the U.S. team deserve to be paid after this?
They've got two years to negotiate. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Fashion-police violation: No more letting the U.S. players'
wives and girlfriends not only dress alike, but color-coordinate
with the guys. There's nothing to coordinate with those tablecloths
the players wore Sunday. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Marvin, hey what 'cha doin' now? Take that $1 billion that's
burning a hole in your pocket and buy your kids an Arena League
trinket instead. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Stephen Davis is NOT someone you thought about drafting on
your rotisserie team. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ We heard the thing that impressed Cal fans most about
freshman QB Kyle Boller was when he dropped Arizona State's
231-pound defensive end !Eric Fields with a solo tackle to prevent
him from returning a fumble into what could have been a
game-winning touchdown late in Saturday's contest. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Whine-a-like lookalikes: Rich Neuheisel and Danny Ainge. . .
.
</P>
<P>
   __ There IS a new Lakers uniform and it'll be unveiled this
week. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Tim Belcher, who started the decade with the Dodgers and will
end it as property of the Angels, will finish with the most losses
(115) and second-most home runs allowed (226) among all big-league
pitchers in the '90s. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Someone mentioned in ``For Love of the Game'' it's
unbelievable that Kevin Costner's character, Billy Chapel, has an
8-11 record despite his 3.55 ERA. One, he pitches for the Tigers.
Two, Houston's Nolan Ryan won the ERA title in 1987 (2.76) and led
the league in Ks (270) to go with his 8-16 mark. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ For the record, the Daily News extended an invitation to
Felix Trinidad to swing by the office and watch a tape of his
recent victory over Oscar De La Hoya. He respectfully declined but
offered the following quote: ``I still think I won. . . . Did you
think I'd change my mind or something?''
</P>
</TEXT>
