<P>
   1. THE COLLECTOR By Deborah Solomon - From The New York Times
Magazine ``Sensation: Young British Artists From the Saatchi
Collection,'' opened at the Royal Academy of Arts in London, two
years ago, and academicians resigned in disgust, protesters hurled
eggs and radio news bulletins led off with dispatches from ``the
Royal Academy of Porn,'' as The Daily Mail rechristened the museum.
This year in New York the show was expected to be much less
controversial when it opened at the Brooklyn Museum of Art, on Oct.
2. The prior week, however, Mayor Rudolph Giuliani called the
artwork ``sick stuff'' and threatened to cut off the museum's
funding if it didn't cancel the show - pretty much assuring that
Saatchi's collection, yet again, will be a smash hit. 
