----------------------------------------------------2. GEORGE C.
SCOTT: ACTING WAS ALL THERE WAS By Ivor Davis (Includes a color
photo, available electronically or in hard copy, of the late George
C. Scott as he appeared in ``12 Angry Men.'') - 1,400 words A
special appreciation of actor George C. Scott, including
never-before-published excerpts from one of Scott's final
interviews, conducted earlier this year. Scott looks back on his
career, explains his philosophy of acting and remembers the
director Stanley Kubrick, who directed Scott's personal favorite of
his own films - ``Dr. Strangelove'' (1964) - and why he refused
Kubrick's offer to appear in the classic film,``2001.'' 
