 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE COMMENTARY BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These columns for release Tuesday, September 28, 1999 are moving
today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   JOEMURRAY-COLUMN _ ANGELINA COUNTY, Texas _ This letter comes
from a longtime friend, Susie Blair of Alexandria, La., in response
to a recent column on a scary plane ride I experienced. Hers is a
better story than mine. (Murray, Cox News Service) MOVED FRIDAY.
</P>
<P>
   GEEWAX-Y2K-COLUMN _ WASHINGTON _ Americans won't know for
another three months whether the Y2K software problem will cause
serious computer disruptions on New Year's Day, but optimists
already are looking beyond 1-1-00 to see the bright side of the
bug. (Geewax, Cox News Service). MOVED THURSDAY
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ Anyone who's tried it lately
knows that air travel is no longer fun. Airports are zoos and
airline employees act like they've forgotten who's paying their
salaries. If it weren't for Toledo Express, I think I'd give all of
my business to Amtrak. (Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   LANE-COLUMN _ DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. _ Biographer Edmund Morris may
not be the last writer reduced to pretending he really knew what
was behind the screen. Media Age politics probably will drive
others to even stranger devices. (Lane, Daytona Beach News-Journal)
MOVED
</P>
<P>
   COXNET BUDGET INFORMATION FOR SUBSCRIBERS OF THE NYT NEWS
SERVICE
</P>
<P>
   Spot news budgets move daily at 2 p.m. and 6 p.m. Eastern.
Additionally, separate features and commentary budgets move at 10
a.m., and sports and business budgets at 6 p.m. Additional updates
are possible if news developments warrant.
</P>
<P>
   All times are Eastern unless otherwise noted. If stories will
move after 8 p.m., an ETA will be given.
</P>
