<HEADLINE>
`MUMMY' A GREAT DVD; `ALVIN' GOOD FOR KIDS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``The Mummy'' (DVD) _ This is a bad movie but a
great DVD. Forget all the silliness of Brendan Fraser's
Egyptological mumbo-jumbo and head straight for the ``Building a
Better Mummy'' documentary on the special effects wizardry. There's
also an archaeological archive that's very well done with sharp
graphics and helpful facts.
</P>
<P>
   ``Alvin and the Chipmunks Meet Frankenstein'' _ If parents can
stand the voices of the chattering chipmunks, the kids will
probably go for this unfrightening Frankenstein.
</P>
<P>
   ``The McCourts of New York'' _ Frank and Malachy McCourt, the
literary brothers, tell their tales in this marvelous story of
poverty made survivable through humor. Angela, their mother and the
title figure in Frank's best-seller, ``Angela's Ashes,'' might not
like the revelations, but that's what helps make the film so sharp
and true.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING SOON ON DVD: ``The Unbearable Lightness of Being'' _
Philip Kaufman's magnificent interpretation of Milan Kundera's
brilliant novel comes stunningly alive in the DVD Criterion edition
of the 1988 film. Daniel Day-Lewis, Juliette Binoche, and Lena Olin
star in a love triangle set against the 1968 Soviet invasion of
Prague. As the title states, it's not that life is unbearably
heavy, but too light. On the commentary track _ Kaufman, Olin, and
screenwriter Jean-Claude Carriere.
</P>
<P>
   ``Pink Floyd: The Wall'' _ Alan Parker's cult ode to the music
of Pink Floyd comes with everything imaginable in the DVD version.
Added footage and a transfer directly from the wide screen
interpositive make the rock epic look better than ever. Also, two
documentaries _ ``The Other Side of The Wall,'' on the making of
the film, and a look back on the film's continued appeal in
``Retrospective.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Oct. 5: ``Lolita'' (1999 version),
``Detour,'' ``Still Life,'' ``Scooby-Doo and the Witch's Ghost.''
Oct. 12: ``The Rage: Carrie 2,'' ``Shakespeare's Women &AMP; Claire
Bloom,'' ``The Hunting of the Snark,'' ``Just a Little Harmless
Sex,'' ``Ten Things I Hate About You,'' ``And Baby Makes Two.''
Oct. 19: ``The Wizard of Oz'' (remastered and DVD), ``Existenz,''
``The Nuttiest Nutcracker,'' ``Color of Courage,'' ``Children of
the Corn 6,'' ``Metroland,'' ``Life,'' ``A Walk on the Moon.'' Oct.
26: ``The Blair Witch Project,'' ``Tactical Assault,'' ``The
Velocity of Gary,'' ``Hideous Kinky,'' ``Arlington Road.'' Nov. 9:
``Life is Beautiful'' (dubbed English language version),
``Instinct,'' ``The Castle,'' ``Heaven,'' ``Break Up,'' ``Rogue
Trader.'' Nov. 30: ``Wild Wild West.''
</P>
