 ART ADV.: Photos with AFFLUENT-BACKPACKER and GENOME-MAPPING are
being transmitted to NYT Photo Service subscribers.  
 For Immediate Release  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following FEATURE stories for
use by NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   EU-CABINET (London) _ As it appoints new commissioners, the
15-nation European Union faces a challenge in improving its
tarnished image after the forced resignations of previous Cabinet
members last spring over allegations of mismanagement and
corruption. By Kevin Cullen. 860 words.
</P>
<P>
   MILOSEVIC-KOSOVO (Belgrade) _ The nightly demonstrations against
Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic have had little effect. Each
day he grows stronger on the apathy of his people. By John
Donnelly. 750 words.
</P>
<P>
   AFFLUENT-BACKPACKER (Windhoek, Namibia) _ The influx of older,
more affluent backpackers causes disruptions in hostels worldwide
and in budget guidebooks. Also at odds are the upper-class traveler
and the traditional backpacker. By Beth Daley. 1300 words. PHOTO (i
and a coding)
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-ISLAM (Kafr Kana, Israel) _ Israeli Arabs are turning to
an organization with roots in almost every Arab town in Israel to
counter decades of neglect and discrimination. By Aliza Marcus.
1,000 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   GENOME-MAPPING (Undated) Work under way in laboratories from
Cambridge to Tokyo to discover the genetic ``Book of Life'' is
almost certain to ignite a revolution in medicine in the early 21st
century. By Aaron Zitner and Richard Saltus. PHOTO (2 takes; a and
f coding)
</P>
<P>
   LEFAVE-JAIL (Boston) _ Cheryl Amirault LeFave is preparing to
return to complete her prison sentence in the Fells Acres child
abuse case. She shudders at the thought, yet admits to having some
warm memories of her previous incarceration. By Sacha Pfeiffer.
1150 words.
</P>
<P>
   NC-FLOOD (Princeville, N.C.) _ A small town in North Carolina
struggles to recover from Hurricane Floyd, one life and one farm at
a time. By Bob Hohler. 1290 words.
</P>
<P>
   BRADLEY-CANDIDATE (Undated) _ After months of disciplined
campaigning, Bill Bradley has crossed the magical divide and has
emerged as a formidable foe to Al Gore. By Scot Lehigh. 1500 words.
