providers introduce services that escalate a price war. AOL U.K.,
part of a joint venture between AOL and Bertelsmann, says its
subscribers who pay a monthly fee would enjoy a reduced flat rate
of a penny (1.6 cents) a minute for all their calls to the Web.
Freeserve, meanwhile, has begun a plan to let users earn up to 10
hours of free Internet calls a month if they spend a minimum on
other calls via its partner, Energis. By Andrew ross Sorkin.
</P>
