<P>
   SCI-QUAKE-RISK (Undated) _ More bad luck is coming, experts
agree. Even though the rate of earthquakes over time seems to be
more or less unchanging, the world's population explosion means
that more people are moving into quake zones, which are often near
coasts. The result is the prospect of continuing trauma as urban
areas erupt with what seems like nearly endless bursts of
destruction. By William J. Broad.
</P>
