Nancy Reagan's breast cancer stimulated a rush for mammography,
Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg's recently diagnosed
colon cancer should jolt all women (and men) over 50 _ and some
younger people as well _ to take advantage of the tests that can
detect this disease while it is still curable, perhaps even before
it has become cancer. By Jane E. Brody.
