   &UR; HEALTH/SCIENCE (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   SCI-OLDER-COLUMN (Undated) -- Age-related weight gain is so
common that most consider it inevitable. But the most important
determinant of weight is basal metabolism -- the rate at which we
burn calories while at rest. By Richard A. Knox. (2 takes)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-MENINGITIS (Undated) _ Most public health experts believed
bacterial meningitis was too rare to recommend vaccination. Now,
after an alarming increase of the disease among college students,
some some say freshmen should be vaccinated. By Karen Hsu. 1245
words.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-QUESTIONS (Undated) _ Why does it feel like we're still
spinning after we stop? By David Ropeik.
</P>
