street in this town have been missing for over five months, ever
since Serb police forced them out from their apartments and
separated them from their wives and children in the street below.
On Monday, their relatives were called to the main police station
here and were told by French gendarmes of the men's fate. It seems
that minutes after the women and children were ordered to flee on
that terrible day, April 14, the men were all executed. The news
brought to an end the families' long search for their menfolk, and
a conclusion to the extensive three-month investigation by the
French. The case is seen as a first in Kosovo where foreign
investigators have conducted a complete investigation, working from
the first reports of missing people to finding a mass grave and
arresting suspects. By Carlotta Gall.
