<P>
   DELL-EXPANDING _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Dell Computer Corp. is
reinventing itself right before our eyes. No longer statisfied to
be just a PC maker _ with profit margins shrinking and the U.S.
market reaching saturation. Monday morning, Dell and IBM announced
an agreement that will make IBM Global Services a strategic
provider of computer-related services to Dell customers. (Mahoney,
Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   HUFFY _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Huffy Corp. said Monday that strong
competition from China will force it to cease U.S. bicycle
manufacturing and take a big charge against earnings. Another key
part of Dayton's manufacturing history bites the dust. (Hulsey,
Tresslar, Dayton Daily News)
</P>
