<P>
   BBN-BRAVES _ What's left for the Braves after clinching the
National League East division title Sunday in Montreal? There are
two key things to play for as they enter Tuesday's three-game
series against the Mets - playing the role of spoiler as the Mets
fight for the wild card and preparing the team for the playoffs,
which begin next week. (Stinson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   FOOTBALL/COLLEGES
</P>
<P>
   VOLS-CHEATING _ Saturday's 17-16 near loss to Memphis appears to
be the least of Tennessee's problems. A seven-week investigation by
ESPN revealed evidence of academic fraud involving four players,
reshirt freshmen this year. Internal documents indicate papers were
written by tutors for some players and that Tennessee officials
were made aware of potential problems and took no action.
(Barnhart, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-LSU _ LSU feature advancing Saturday's game against Georgia.
(Towers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 14.
</P>
