several weeks cast yet another pall over a Falcons team that is
beginning to look a lot like yesteryear. (Winkeljohn, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 13.
</P>
<P>
   HOCKEY
</P>
<P>
   HKN-THRASHERS _ The new overtime rules in the NHL should be a
hit with the fans, but they will likely work against the Thrashers.
Four-on-four gives the edge to teams with a lot of skilled
offensive players, something Atlanta doesn't have. The NHL went to
four-on-four in hopes of having more games decided in the
five-minute sudden-death period, rather than remain tied. (Schultz,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
