<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   OLY-IOC _ The International Olympic Committee said Monday it
will investigate improprieties by its members during Atlanta's bid
for the 1996 Summer Games. However, the investigation, which will
be conducted by the IOC's new ethics commission, is not likely to
exact any more changes in what one congressman calls a ``culture of
corruption'' within the bidding process. (Tunrer, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
