</P>
<P>
   GINGRICH _ With a flurry of direct mail and a decisive vision
for the future, private citizen Newt Gingrich's new political
action committee raised more than $1 million the first half of this
year. But a July divorce declaration and rumors of an affair with a
33-year-old congressional aide could put Gingrich's future
fund-raising exploits at risk. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30.
</P>
<P>
   BRADLEY-PROFILE _ Personal profile of Bill Bradley. (Foskett,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   SURPLUS _ WASHINGTON _ President Clinton on Monday announced
this year's budget surplus is estimated to hit at least $115
billion, the largest in American history. So what does it mean for
shoring up Social Security? And will it impact the nation's
still-staggering debt? An explainer. (Deans, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   LEASES _ GREENVILLE, N.C. _ Latest on East Carolina University
student housing. ECU's student government has hired an attorney to
help students with leasing issues and submerged apartments. What
rights do students and leasees have to get out from damaged
apartments? (Batchelor, Greenville Daily Reflector).
</P>
<P>
   UTILITIES _ GREENVILLE, N.C. _ After saving the city's power and
water supplies, Greenville Utilities is trying to pick up the
pieces of its submerged operations center. (Bryant, Greenville
Daily Reflector).
</P>
<P>
   TUTU _ Bishop Desmond Tutu delivers a keynote speech at Holy
Innocents' Episcopal School in metro Atlanta today. (Brett, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
