in South Carolina and a foreign-policy address in California. By
JEFF BARKER. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
MAHONEY - Former Arizona Secretary of State and Kennedy scholar
Richard Mahoney has just published a new book detailing the
relationship between Jack and Bobby Kennedy and their father,
Joseph P. Kennedy Sr. The three were not the unified political
``juggernaut'' that history has painted them, Mahoney says in
``Sons &AMP; Brothers: The Days of Jack and Robert Kennedy.'' But Joe
Sr. was a loving if controlling father devoted to his sons - one a
man of great style and acquired substance, and the other, Bobby,
the moral voice of the famous family. By BARBARA YOST. Story will
move in the ``L'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
MONTINI-COLUMN _ (Phoenix) Investigators, prosecutors and officers
for the most powerful, most highly-trained and most technologically
advanced military organanization on the planet are taking most of a
year to determine whether Arizona legislatory and U.S. Army Reserve
Lt. Steve May is a homosexual. ``I am,'' May says. By EJ MONTINI.
Story will move in the ``A'' and ``K'' categories. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
