A8025 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u f BC-CMGI-IPO-BOS &LR;      09-27 0332
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CMGI-IPO-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CMGI TO GO PUBLIC WITH ALTAVISTA IN JANUARY 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds.: 1stUp.com is cq)   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By HIAWATHA BRAY  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   CMGI Inc. is planning to take its Wide Web search service
AltaVista public in January.
</P>
<P>
   CMGI chairman David Wetherell talking to reporters in a
conference call Monday about the company's fourth-quarter earnings,
said AltaVista would file for an initial public offering after
CMGI's first quarter, which ends Oct. 31.
</P>
<P>
   CMGI, which invests in up-and-coming Internet firms, completed
its $2.3 billion purchase of a majority stake in AltaVista in
August. The company said then that it wanted eventually to spin the
search engine off as a separate company.
</P>
<P>
   Before selling AltaVista to CMGI, Compaq also had plans to take
the search service public as a way to profit from the Internet
boom.
</P>
<P>
   Besides its AltaVista announcement, the company said it produced
fourth-quarter profits of $452.7 million, largely due to a $661.2
million pretax gain from the sale of GeoCities to Yahoo Inc. for
$2.87 billion in May. CMGI owned 27 percent of GeoCities. Apart
from the GeoCities deal and other one-time gains, CMGI lost $51.4
million for the quarter.
</P>
<P>
   Apart from the GeoCities bounty, CMGI's fourth-quarter revenues
were $53.6 million, up from $25.9 million the year before. Revenues
for the fiscal year were $175.7 million, compared to $81.9 million
in 1998. Total 1999 net income was $476.2 million, compared with
$31.9 million in 1998.
</P>
<P>
   Also Monday, CMGI announced it would acquire Palo Alto,
Calif.-based 1stUp.com, which provides free advertising-supported
Internet access to consumers, in a stock-swap transaction. No
further details of the deal were released.
</P>
<P>
   CMGI shares jumped 8 5/16, or 9.8 percent, to 93 1/8, and the
stock rose as high as 95 after the close of markets. CMGI is based
in Andover, Mass.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
(Wire service material News was used to prepare this report.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-27-99 1919EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
