</P>
<P>
   DIGITAL-HOLLYWOOD (Los Angeles) _ Participants at the ``Digital
Hollywood'' conference, which focuses on high tech's influence on
entertainment world and runs through Thursday in Los Angeles, see
digital production as a way to create local jobs for people losing
work because of runaway production to cheaper venues like
Vancouver. Also Monday, The Academy of Television Arts &AMP; Sciences
in North Hollywood was hosting a conference on stemming the tide of
runaway production, including congressmen, state representatives
and industry leaders. By David Bloom and Robert Monroe. (Will move
in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news file.)
</P>
<P>
   LA-ARENA (Los Angeles) _ The Los Angeles City Council's Ad Hoc
Committee on the Los Angeles Arena Proposal will discuss traffic
and security issues relating to the new Staples Center and a report
on the facility from the city's chief legislative analyst. By Rick
Orlov. (Will move in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news
file.)
</P>
<P>
   HOLLYWOOD-COMEBACK (Los Angeles) _ The Hollywood renaissance
continues. Retail sales, hotel occupancy rates and just about every
other economic indicator was higher in the Hollywood Business
Improvement District in 1998 compared to '97, according to an
economic survey released Monday. Hotel occupancy increased 32
percent and rates jumped 8 percent; office lease rates increased 12
percent; pedestrian counts increased 5 percent; and retail and
restaurant revenue increased 4 and 5 percent, respectively. By
Chris Sieroty. (Will move in the ``f'' financial and ``e''
entertainment wire files.)
</P>
<P>
   XIRCOM-ACQUISITION (Los Angeles) _ Xircom Inc. went on a
shopping spree Monday, announcing the purchase of a line of
products and another company for a collective $36.5 million in
cash, stock and debt. Xircom will take a charge of $3 million to $4
million against its earnings this quarter to cover the acquisition
of the Rex line of electronic organizers from Franklin Electronic
Publishers. In addition, the company will trade 323,905 shares of
its own stock for all outstanding shares of Entregas Technologies,
a private company from Lake Forest in Orange County. By Jason Z.
Cohen. (Will move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
