   SPEND-CONGRESS (Washington) _ A $500 billion confrontation
between the Clinton administration and Congress begins to build, as
the White House, vowing to veto Republican spending bills, sets a
three-week deadline for a budget deal. This is a fight that
President Clinton has reason to relish, and Republicans in Congress
