<P>
   KOSOVO-ARRESTS (Mitrovica, Kosovo) _ The French police notify
the families of 26 men missing from town for five months that they
had been killed by Serbs, and dumped in a mass grave. The French
have arrested four suspects. This case marks the first time in
Kosovo that foreigners have conducted a complete investigation,
working from the first reports of missing people to finding the
grave and making arrests. It also demonstrates a greater commitment
than in the former Yugoslavia to catch those responsible for war
crimes. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.) By
