   Here are tonight's other regular features:
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ Stock prices rebounded a bit Monday as
investors became selective buyers of shares that were particularly
hard-hit by last week's steep sell-off. Still, major market
averages closed well under their session highs, and some analysts
said conditions were still unsettled, suggesting that prices could
fall a bit further. By Kenneth N. Gilpin.
</P>
<P>
   (The story has moved.)
