Malathion for spraying from helicopters earlier this month. The
outbreak of a mosquito-borne illness that killed at least three
people in New York was not caused by St. Louis encephalitis at all,
but rather a form of the West Nile virus that has previously never
been diagnosed in the Western Hemisphere, government health
