a surprise plan to put a cap on their planned sales of gold
bullion. Gold peaked at $285 an ounce in London Monday, more than
$16 above the price of $268.60 in late trading Friday. The price
fell back to $278.90 in late London trading and was $281.90 in New
York late Monday. (New York Times Photo)
