though the rate of earthquakes over time seems to be more or less
unchanging, the world's population explosion means that more people
are moving into quake zones. The result, experts say, is the
prospect of continuing trauma as urban areas erupt with what seems
like nearly endless bursts of destruction. (David L. Ryan/New York
